#1 Resected recurrent rectal adenocarcinoma
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Patrick Service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Harrison and Dr. Rodriguez, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
I will ask Dr. Rodriguez to see Ms. Kent prior to hospital dismissal for formal treatment recommendations.  She does have a prior history of significant vasospasm accompanying infusional 5-FU.  Please see Dr. Bourgeois note for full plan of care.  At this point, I will not make follow-up appointments for Ms. Kent to return as she has a local medical oncologist she wishes to follow-up with.  Certainly, if the need arises in the future, I am more than happy to help facilitate care.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

